k\binom{n\vphantom{1}}{k}=n\binom{n-1}{k-1}
 \begin{align} \sum_{k=0}^nk\binom{n}{k}p^k(1-p)^{n-k} &=\sum_{k=0}^nn\binom{n-1}{k-1}p^k(1-p)^{n-k}\\ &=np\sum_{k=0}^n\binom{n-1}{k-1}p^{k-1}(1-p)^{n-k}\\ &=np\,\Big(p+(1-p)\Big)^{n-1}\\[12pt] &=np \end{align} 
